experience.description:
Management:
  • Created a management, accounting and reporting system with "0";
  • Managed the financial unit of the company (operations department, accounting, cashpoints, IT);
  • Interacted with potential and existing investors.
Finance:
  • Prepared the company's annual budget;
  • Controlled financial flows in the company (payment calendar, rolling cash flow, etc.);
  • Was responsible for monthly, quarterly and annual management reports for the company's management;
  • Presented and defended financial models and business plans for potential investors.
Automation:
  • Automation of financial, accounting and management accounting in the organization based on 1C: ERP;
  • Implementation of the Way 4 electronic wallet transaction accounting program;
  • Integration of 1C:ERP with the Way 4 electronic payment management program.
Achievements:
  • Created a well-established financial system in the organization;
  • Provided high capitalization of the company.

Management:
  • Finance department management;
  • Cooperation with others departments of the company;
  • Analysis and management of financial resources, planning and control of cash flow, budget of income and expenses, budgeting;
Accounting and tax accounting:
  • Monitoring the work of the accounting Department for the group of companies; Management accounting. Passing the audit;
  • Cooperation with state authorities including regular statements (IFNS, custom, funds);
  • Contracts approval to avoid tax risks.
Finance: 
  • Organized work with banks (obtaining Bank guarantees, overdrafts, credit lines, etc.);
  • Developed, protected and controlled the annual budget for the group of companies with a turnover of more than 5 billion rubles;
     • Created and controlled the payment calendar, found funds to cover cash gaps in the amount of 50 million rubles;
     • Participated in mergers of companies with a total turnover of up to 1 billion rubles.
Achievements: 
     • Received revolving credit lines and an overdraft of 20 million USD and 50 million RUB;
     • Positive audit report on the results of 2017;
     • Reduced the time for passing the annual audit by a month;
     • Created a current management accounting system in an international group of companies (Russia-Kazakhstan).

Management:
  • Finance department management, foreign trade activity;
  • Cooperation with others departments of the company. Total number of employees 50;
  • Analyzing and controlling financial resources, cash flow, budgeting;
  • Cooperation with counteragents concerning consulting, legal support, insurance, education.
Accounting and tax accounting:
  • Adaptation of accounting and tax policies and internal regulations;
  • Organized successful completion of the annual audit;
  • Financial reports and statements to HQ and for the management;
  • Was responsible for interaction with state authorities (tax, customs, funds);
  • Improved the system to evaluate contracts for the absence of tax risks.
Finance: 
     • Supervised interaction with banks for obtaining Bank guarantees, deposits, etc.;
     • Developed and implemented a procedure for evaluating potential customers to set the credit limit. Monitoring financial conditions of current customers (first of all, rent customers). Assessment of new suppliers;
    • Analyzing mutual settlements (including trade and other receivables).
Automation: 
  • Improvement of 1C: Accounting and 1C: Trade;
  • Tuning automatic interchange between 1C: Accounting and 1C: Trade.
Achievements:
  • Reduced the deadline for submitting a monthly report to HQ by 2 times;
  • Received Bank guarantees in two banks (SOVCOMBANK, UniCredit Bank) in the amount of 100 million rubles;
  • Introduced the methodology of the counteragent assessment (customers and suppliers);
  • Received positive auditors conclusion (2016) earlier than in previous periods.

Management:
• General Manager's duties performed during his leave. From 01.11.2013 until 18.12.2013 – General Manager;
• Finance department management;
• Cooperation with auditors/annual IFRS audit. Cooperation with tax consulters, lawyers concerning issues connected with labor, civil, custom legislation.   
          Accounting and tax accounting:
            • Formed the company's accounting policy for accounting, tax accounting and IFRS purposes;
            • Verifying export VAT (0%) (Kazakhstan, Belarus, Kyrgyzstan);
            • Controlling and bookkeeping, tax accounting in full size;
            • Controlling trade receivables and payables (and other receivables and payables);
            • Tax planning, tax optimization;
            • Regularly communication with financial management of HQ concerning taxation, accounting (RAS and IFRS) and financial statement;
            • Monthly closing performed for the Headquarters by the 1st date of each month.
          Finance:
            • Communication with banks. Currency hedging (forward contracts, option contracts), overdraft, credit lines (Raiffeisenbank, COMMERZBANK);     
            • Calculated and controlled the financial results of import contracts;
            • Preparing monthly management reports with tight deadline (cash flow, P&L, Balance sheet), forming cash flow, budgeting;
            • Preparing management statement of the company in compliance with IFRS (monthly/quarterly/annual).
         Automation:
            • Automation of data exchange between accounting programs; work with IT specialists, improvements;
            • Tuning automatic interchange between 1C: Accounting and 1C: Trade;
            • Creation of non-typical reports to form the reports needed for HQ quickly;
Achievements:
• Organized and introduced accounting in compliance with RAS and IFRS;
• Implemented quality management system ISO 9001(audit with subsequent receiving of the accordance certificate ISO9001);
• Reduced the period of submitting management statement to HQ from 10 to 3 working days;
• Received the auditor’s conclusion in compliance with RAS and IFRS until the end of January of the next year;
• Created controlling and hedging currency risk system.
